              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "BCINT"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The absolute values of the differential cross",
                "sections were obtained using the charge collected in",
                "the Faraday cup, the target thickness and solid angles",
                "accurately measured for each telescope."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Self-supporting vanadium target was used. Target",
                "thickness was 1.98+-0.04 mg/cm2."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Deuteron spectra were analyzed using a Gaussian",
                "peak-fitting programme which provided peak centroids,",
                "integrals and background subtraction for each deuteron",
                "group.",
                "The energy calibration of the spectra was based on the",
                "0.437,2.317 and 3.194 MeV levels, excitation energies",
                "of which were accurately measured in the",
                "51V(n,gamma)52V reaction. (see REL-REF).",
                "The relatively weak contaminant peak of the 12C(t,d)",
                "reaction to the 3.854 MeV state in 13C was used as a",
                "reference in the high excitation region."
              ]
            }
          ],
